0 thog2/remainder/codec.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Reference adjacent-representable decoder, directional code steps and later packed codec.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/store.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Int8 and packed storage, registration, validation and checkpoint state.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/effective_weight.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Straight-through effective-weight construction and disabled-path bypass.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/projection.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Common projection interface and geometry-specific adapters.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/optimizer_reference.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 R1 FP32-master AdamW reference optimiser.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/optimizer_factored.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 R2 factored-RMS stochastic integer optimiser.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/autograd.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Full-matrix gradient hook and later streamed custom backward.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\clcbpat4\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 thog2/remainder/telemetry.py\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Remainder state, gradient, update and memory metrics.\cell\row\n\trowd\trgaph90\trleft0\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx3300\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\clpadl90\clpadr90\clpadt70\clpadb70\cellx9400\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 tests/remainder/\cell\pard\intbl\f0\fs18\sb0\sa0 Unit, integration, resume, dtype and memory tests.\cell\row\n\pard\sa140\par\n\pard\sb120\sa160\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat7\f0\fs22 \b Integration rule\b0\line Use the existing spectral materialiser and training lifecycle. Do not replicate them inside the remainder package.\par\n\page\n\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\keepn\cf1\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 5  Stage 0 - contracts, decoder, projector and diagnostic\b0\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 5.1  Purpose\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Establish the contracts that every later stage depends upon. This stage changes no training behaviour.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 5.2  Pre-code deliverable\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Commit a Stage 0 Test Plan before production code. It must enumerate the decoder, addressing, projection and configuration tests.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 5.3  Implementation work\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 1.\tab Add remainder configuration objects and validation. The default mode is off.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 2.\tab Define the six legal tensor-family keys: attn_q, attn_k, attn_v, attn_out, mlp_in and mlp_out.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 3.\tab Define canonical final-matrix views independent of qkv packing, head reshaping and materialisation order.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 4.\tab Implement the literal repeated-nextafter decoder for FP16, BF16 and FP32.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 5.\tab Implement directional code-step calculation and outward-bound masking.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 6.\tab Add the common project_weight_gradient interface.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 7.\tab Implement CHEBY projection adapters for every existing spectral geometry using the exact forward basis matrices and axis order.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 8.\tab Build a deterministic offline diagnostic for logical widths 1, 2, 3, 4, 6 and 8.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 5.4  Exit evidence\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Decoder results are bitwise identical to the literal nextafter reference, including zero, subnormals, exponent boundaries and maximum finite values.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Single tensor coordinates remain stable across semantic and packed views.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Projected plus rejected gradients reconstruct the original gradient within the specified tolerance.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Projected and rejected components meet the orthogonality tolerance for orthonormal bases.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab All Stage 0 and existing regression tests pass.\par
\pard\sb120\sa160\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat8\f0\fs22 \b Blocker\b0\line Do not proceed if projection is inferred only from tensor shapes. It must be the exact reverse contraction of the active materialiser.\par\n\page\n\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\keepn\cf1\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 6  Stage 1 - forward-only remainder path\b0\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 6.1  Purpose\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Introduce the remainder object into the forward path without attempting to learn it. The goal is to prove storage, addressing, decoding and checkpoint correctness.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 6.2  Implementation work\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 1.\tab Add zero-initialised int8 remainder buffers for the six covered spectral matrix families.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 2.\tab Attach tensor key, shape, bit width, layout and schema metadata.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 3.\tab Implement the straight-through effective-weight builder.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 4.\tab Integrate the builder at each covered linear-weight site.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 5.\tab Add checkpoint save/load for remainder values and metadata.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 6.\tab Add read-only telemetry: non-zero fraction, value histogram, saturation fraction and mean absolute offset.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 6.3  Required tests\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Width zero reproduces the existing logits and loss exactly under the same execution path.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Active mode with all remainder codes equal to zero reproduces the base model.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Changing one code changes exactly one intended effective matrix element.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab All six tensor families and first, middle and final layers are covered.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab Checkpoint round-trip preserves all codes and metadata exactly.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-270\sb0\sa95\bullet\tab CPU, scruffy BF16 and dreedle FP16 smoke tests pass.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 6.4  Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 No backward or optimiser behaviour changes are permitted in this stage. Stage 2 begins only after address correctness and zero-equivalence are beyond doubt.\par
\page\n\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\keepn\cf1\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 7  Stage 2 - gradient routing and R1 reference optimiser\b0\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 7.1  Purpose\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Establish the one-backprop architecture and determine whether the remainder can learn when given familiar, deliberately expensive optimisation. R1 is an optimisation oracle, not the target memory design.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 7.2  One backward pass\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The effective-weight gradient is split into two components. The base path receives the part expressible by the spectral geometry. The remainder path receives what remains.\par
\pard\f2\fs18\li360\ri360\sb80\sa120\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw8\brdrcf4\shading100\cbpat4 effective_gradient = d(loss) / d(effective_weight)\line projected_gradient = project_to_base_span(effective_gradient)\line rejected_gradient  = effective_gradient - projected_gradient\par\n\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 7.3  Implementation work\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 1.\tab Attach a gradient hook to each effective weight.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 2.\tab Compute projected_gradient and rejected_gradient.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 3.\tab Return only projected_gradient to the existing autograd path.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 4.\tab Verify the coefficient gradient against an explicit analysis transform.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 5.\tab Add one FP32 remainder_master tensor for each int8 remainder tensor.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 6.\tab Optimise the masters with ordinary AdamW and then quantise them to bounded signed integer codes.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 7.\tab Add R1 checkpoint, resume and telemetry support.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\li540\fi-360\sb0\sa105 8.\tab Require gradient accumulation equal to one in R1 to keep the reference behaviour unambiguous.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 7.4  Exit gate\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Run a small matched test at widths 0, 2 and 4. Stage 3 begins only if width 4 produces a credible loss improvement and the rejected gradient is demonstrably non-trivial.\par
\pard\sb120\sa160\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat8\f0\fs22 \b Interpretation rule\b0\line If R1 fails, the problem is the representation, decoding or gradient routing. Do not proceed to the custom optimiser.\par\n\page\n\pard\ql\f1\fs30\sb180\sa180\keepn\cf1\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw12\brdrcf2\brsp80\b 8  Stage 3 - target remainder optimiser\b0\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 8.1  Purpose\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 Replace the dense FP32 reference master and dense AdamW moments with an optimiser whose persistent state remains small relative to the low-bit remainder itself.\par
\pard\sb120\sa160\li180\ri180\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw28\brdrcf2\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\brdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf2\shading100\cbpat7\f0\fs22 \b Why this is difficult\b0\line The parameter is a bounded signed integer code, but the incoming rejected gradient is continuous. Small gradients must influence future integer movement without storing a dense floating-point debt tensor. The optimiser must also be reproducible across gradient accumulation, skipped updates and resume.\par\n\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 8.2  Chosen baseline\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The first target optimiser is a factored-RMS stochastic integer updater. It keeps one FP32 second-moment vector per matrix row and one per matrix column. It stores no per-weight floating-point master and no dense first or second moment.\par
