8.5  Gradient accumulation\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 The model keeps the same remainder values throughout an accumulation window. Each microstep contributes a small stochastic integer proposal and row/column squared-gradient observations. The integer proposals are combined into a transient pending step, clamped to the configured maximum, and applied only when the complete optimiser update is accepted.\par
\pard\ql\f1\fs25\sb160\sa100\keepn\cf1\b 8.6  Atomic non-finite handling\b0\par
\pard\ql\f0\fs22\sb0\sa160 A non-finite update is skipped as one transaction. Base AdamW does not step; remainder values do not change; row and column factors do not change; pending steps are discarded; and the remainder RNG is restored to its pre-update state.\par
